      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:44:6",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " الصَّبِيِّ يَسْرِقُ قَالَ يُعْفَى عَنْهُ مَرَّةً فَإِنْ عَادَ قُطِعَتْ أَنَامِلُهُ أَوْ حُكَّتْ حَتَّى تَدْمَى فَإِنْ عَادَ قُطِعَتْ أَصَابِعُهُ فَإِنْ عَادَ قُطِعَ أَسْفَلُ مِنْ ذَلِكَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad and Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, altogether from Ibn Mahboub, from Abdullah Bin Sinan, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> regarding the child who steals. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘He would be excused from it once. So if he repeats, his fingertips would be cut, or they would be scratched until they bleed. So he if repeats, his fingers would be cut. So if he repeats, he would be cut lower than that’."
        ]
      }
    }
